## 🔧 Hardware Setup

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│           Vehicle Electronics               │
│                                             │
│  Battery (60V LiPo)                         │
│       │                                     │
│       ▼                                     │
│  VESC MC75  ──── UART ────  GPS Module      │
│       │              (u-blox, 1Hz, NMEA)    │
│       │                                     │
│       ▼                                     │
│  BLDC Motor                                 │
│       │                                     │
│       ▼                                     │
│  Drivetrain → Rear wheel                    │
│                                             │
│  VESC Tool (PC/laptop) ── USB ── VESC       │
│       └── Log: .csv export (55 columns)     │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**VESC Settings for GPS logging:**
1. `App Settings → GNSS` → enable, set UART port and baud rate to match GPS module
2. `App Settings → IMU` → enable (for roll/pitch/yaw)
3. Power on vehicle **5–10 minutes before** session for GPS cold-start fix
4. Verify: `gnss_posTime > 0` and `gnss_lat != 0.0` before starting lap

---

## 📊 Data Format

VESC MC75 exports semicolon-delimited `.csv` with 55 columns. Key columns used:

| Column | Unit | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `ms_today` | ms | Timestamp |
| `erpm` | ERPM | Electrical RPM |
| `duty_cycle` | — | Throttle duty [-1, 1] |
| `speed_meters_per_sec` | m/s | Calculated wheel speed |
| `tacho_meters` | m | Odometer (cumulative) |
| `current_in` | A | Battery current draw |
| `watt_hours_used` | Wh | Cumulative energy used |
| `input_voltage` | V | Battery voltage |
| `temp_mos_max` | °C | Peak MOSFET temperature |
| `gnss_lat` | deg | GPS latitude |
| `gnss_lon` | deg | GPS longitude |
| `gnss_alt` | m | GPS altitude |
| `gnss_hAcc` | m | Horizontal accuracy |
| `gnss_posTime` | ms | GPS fix timestamp (-1 = no fix) |

