## 📈 Results

### End-to-End Pipeline Output

```
Input:   Raw VESC telemetry, 6 laps, Surabaya track
Output:  Optimal duty_cycle[20] lookup table

┌────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  GA Optimal Profile                        │
│  eff = 1.671 Wh/km                        │
│  v_avg = 10.2 km/h  ✓ (≥ 10)             │
│  v_max = 37.3 km/h  ✓ (≤ 45)             │
│                                            │
│  Chromosome:                               │
│  [0.08, 0.00, 0.04, 0.00, 0.08, 0.10,    │
│   0.05, 0.01, 0.01, 0.00, 0.01, 0.01,    │
│   0.03, 0.00, 0.00, 0.04, 0.01, 0.05,    │
│   0.08, 0.01]                             │
└────────────────────────────────────────────┘

PID Correction Layer:
  Kp = 0.0247  |  Ti = 2.644s  |  Ki = 0.0093
  Setpoint = profile[segment_index] * K (m/s)
  Output   = duty_cycle command to VESC
```

### VESC Integration

```python
# Pseudo-code for onboard implementation
import time

PROFILE = [0.082, 0.000, 0.040, ...]  # 20 genes
SEGMENT_DURATION = 10.0               # seconds
Kp, Ti = 0.0247, 2.644

lap_start = time.time()
integral = 0.0

while racing:
    seg = int((time.time() - lap_start) / SEGMENT_DURATION) % 20
    setpoint = PROFILE[seg] * 37.61   # m/s target from GA

    error = setpoint - vesc.get_speed()
    integral += error / Ti
    duty = Kp * (error + integral)

    vesc.set_duty(max(0, min(1, duty)))
```

